    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-23T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296A1/63: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"
                            >Garrett</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-23T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 23, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Your 13, January 20, noon. The Department’s views in this matter are covered
                    by the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of December 29, sent to you from
                    Paris as Department’s No. 1 and the Department’s 28, January 18, 4 p.m., to
                    Paris, which Paris has sent to you. The texts of these are of course strictly
                    confidential and were given to you for your information and for background in
                    your discussions with <persName corresp="#p_GD1">Grandi</persName> or other
                    competent Italian officials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
